507
00:39:04,350 --> 00:39:06,386
What do you want from me?

508
00:39:06,470 --> 00:39:12,625
If you could let her
on the ice, I'd appreciate it.

509
00:39:12,710 --> 00:39:14,507
1 0 minutes, 1 0 bucks.

510
00:39:14,590 --> 00:39:16,501
How about eight bucks?

511
00:39:16,590 --> 00:39:18,660
Come on, it's Thanksgiving.

512
00:39:18,750 --> 00:39:20,741
All right, nine bucks.

513
00:39:20,830 --> 00:39:23,981
You'll have the ice
to yourself. 1 0 bucks.

514
00:39:25,390 --> 00:39:27,346
Give me the blades.

515
00:39:27,630 --> 00:39:29,700
Aren't you skating?

516
00:39:29,790 --> 00:39:31,746
I ain't skated since I was 1 5.

517
00:39:31,830 --> 00:39:34,105
That's when I started fighting.

518
00:39:34,190 --> 00:39:36,784
Skating's bad for the ankles.

519
00:39:36,870 --> 00:39:39,987
You're a pretty good
skater, are you?

520
00:39:40,070 --> 00:39:42,584
Like I was saying,

521
00:39:42,670 --> 00:39:46,549
fighting used to be tops
for me, but no more.

522
00:39:46,630 --> 00:39:51,101
All I wanted was to prove
I could make a good pro.

523
00:39:51,190 --> 00:39:53,181
You never got the chance?

524
00:39:53,270 --> 00:39:56,580
I ain't crying about it
because I still fight.

525
00:39:56,670 --> 00:39:59,901
- But I'm a southpaw.
- What's a southpaw?

526
00:39:59,990 --> 00:40:01,981
It means you're left-handed.

527
00:40:02,070 --> 00:40:05,187
Other guys,
it throws their timing off,

528
00:40:05,270 --> 00:40:07,545
makes them look awkward.

529
00:40:07,630 --> 00:40:10,190
You know where
southpaw came from?

530
00:40:10,270 --> 00:40:12,101
A long time ago,

531
00:40:12,190 --> 00:40:16,468
there was this guy fighting
around Philadelphia.

532
00:40:16,550 --> 00:40:19,223
He was left-handed,

533
00:40:19,310 --> 00:40:22,108
and his arm was facing
towards New Jersey.

534
00:40:22,190 --> 00:40:25,944
That's south, so naturally
they called him south paw.

535
00:40:26,030 --> 00:40:30,262
Southpaw, South Jersey,
South Camden, southpaw.

536
00:40:31,110 --> 00:40:34,420
Things probably
worked out for the best.

537
00:40:34,510 --> 00:40:37,070
Never got a chance
because you're left-handed?

538
00:40:37,150 --> 00:40:38,947
That's absolutely true.

539
00:40:39,030 --> 00:40:40,258
Watch out.

540
00:40:43,110 --> 00:40:45,226
I just dislocated my finger.

541
00:40:45,310 --> 00:40:46,948
Look at that.

542
00:40:47,470 --> 00:40:51,509
It ain't your fault.
That's an old wound.

543
00:40:51,590 --> 00:40:55,219
You see that?
It bends like that.

544
00:40:55,310 --> 00:40:57,870
Push the button. Bong.
It works.

545
00:40:57,950 --> 00:41:00,066
I'll show you something.

546
00:41:00,150 --> 00:41:01,742
Seven minutes!

547
00:41:01,830 --> 00:41:03,821
I keep pictures of my fights.

548
00:41:03,910 --> 00:41:06,902
I done it in the
Baby Crenshaw fight.

549
00:41:06,990 --> 00:41:10,062
I broke both my hands
on his face.

550
00:41:10,150 --> 00:41:14,029
I lost that fight,
but that's a nice picture.

551
00:41:15,110 --> 00:41:17,066
You having a good time?

552
00:41:18,030 --> 00:41:21,022
You can see I ain't
too graceful.

553
00:41:21,110 --> 00:41:22,748
I don't move well.

554
00:41:22,830 --> 00:41:25,219
But I can really hit hard.

555
00:41:25,310 --> 00:41:28,063
But nobody wants
to fight no southpaw.

556
00:41:33,790 --> 00:41:36,827
You know how I got
started in fighting?

557
00:41:36,910 --> 00:41:38,184
No.

558
00:41:38,270 --> 00:41:40,181
Am I talking too loud?

559
00:41:40,270 --> 00:41:42,101
Three minutes!

560
00:41:42,190 --> 00:41:45,978
My father -
he was never too smart -

561
00:41:46,070 --> 00:41:49,619
He says to me, "You weren't
born with much of a brain,

562
00:41:49,710 --> 00:41:51,587
"so you better use your body."

563
00:41:51,670 --> 00:41:54,662
So I become a fighter,
you know?

564
00:41:54,750 --> 00:41:56,945
Why are you laughing?

565
00:41:57,030 --> 00:42:02,502
- My mother said the opposite.
- What did she say?

566
00:42:02,590 --> 00:42:06,299
She said, "You weren't born
with much of a body,

567
00:42:06,390 --> 00:42:08,904
"so you better
develop your brain."

568
00:42:08,990 --> 00:42:10,582
Yo! Time!

569
00:42:11,230 --> 00:42:13,380
Can I ask you a question?

570
00:42:13,470 --> 00:42:14,789
Absolutely.

571
00:42:14,870 --> 00:42:17,430
Why do you want to fight?

572
00:42:17,510 --> 00:42:20,263
Because
I can't sing or dance.

573
00:42:21,470 --> 00:42:23,222
Don't fall!

574
00:42:23,310 --> 00:42:27,223
I'm pretty good at this.
You like the way I skate?

575
00:42:27,310 --> 00:42:32,020
Last fight I had, with Spider
Rico, he busted my head here.

576
00:42:32,110 --> 00:42:35,739
Things get pretty rough
in the ring.

577
00:42:44,350 --> 00:42:47,865
Some people are very shy
by nature, you know?

578
00:42:47,950 --> 00:42:50,100
I suppose.

579
00:42:51,750 --> 00:42:55,902
I say you're very shy
by nature, you know?

580
00:42:55,990 --> 00:42:57,628
I suppose.

581
00:43:00,150 --> 00:43:03,779
The bum from the dark.
Get a job.

582
00:43:04,070 --> 00:43:07,983
Some people think
being shy is a disease,

583
00:43:08,070 --> 00:43:10,026
but it don't bother me none.

584
00:43:10,110 --> 00:43:12,305
Don't bother me, either.

585
00:43:12,390 --> 00:43:16,508
Why did I bring it up?
Because I'm dumb.

586
00:43:17,670 --> 00:43:21,265
We make a real sharp
couple of coconuts.

587
00:43:21,350 --> 00:43:23,147
I'm dumb, you're shy.

588
00:43:24,270 --> 00:43:28,024
Why would anybody
want to be a fighter?

589
00:43:28,110 --> 00:43:33,343
You got to be a moron
to want to be a fighter.

590
00:43:33,430 --> 00:43:36,866
You're almost guaranteed
to end up a bum.

591
00:43:36,950 --> 00:43:39,384
I don't think you're a bum.

592
00:43:39,470 --> 00:43:43,304
I'm at least half a bum,
but I'll tell you something.

593
00:43:43,390 --> 00:43:47,747
Worst thing about fighting
is the morning after.

594
00:43:47,830 --> 00:43:52,506
The morning after a fight,
you're like a large wound.

595
00:43:52,590 --> 00:43:54,706
I feel like calling a taxi

596
00:43:54,790 --> 00:43:57,862
to take me from the bed
to the bathroom.

597
00:43:57,950 --> 00:44:02,819
Your hair hurts, your eyes hurt,
your face is busted up.

598
00:44:02,910 --> 00:44:04,980
Look at this face... 64 fights.

599
00:44:05,070 --> 00:44:06,947
See that nose?

600
00:44:07,030 --> 00:44:09,669
That nose ain't
never been broken.

601
00:44:09,750 --> 00:44:13,663
I had guys chewing on it,
twisting it, punching it.

602
00:44:13,750 --> 00:44:17,504
These guys are hitting
my nose all the time.

603
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,548
Never broke. I'm proud of that.

604
00:44:20,630 --> 00:44:23,940
- Why do it if it hurts?
- Why do you think?

605
00:44:25,270 --> 00:44:28,660
'Cause you can't sing or dance.

606
00:44:28,750 --> 00:44:31,025
Yeah, something like that.

607
00:44:31,110 --> 00:44:33,146
Want to come inside?

608
00:44:34,670 --> 00:44:36,581
No, I got to go.

609
00:44:36,670 --> 00:44:40,549
Come on. I got these
very rare animals inside.

610
00:44:41,630 --> 00:44:44,019
No, I got to go.

611
00:44:44,110 --> 00:44:48,023
I got to go to
the bathroom. Come on.

612
00:44:48,110 --> 00:44:50,021
No, I got to go.

613
00:44:50,390 --> 00:44:53,223
Is this a face you can trust?

614
00:44:53,310 --> 00:44:56,905
They ought to stick
this face on a stamp.

615
00:44:58,670 --> 00:45:00,740
Come on. Come on in.

616
00:45:05,510 --> 00:45:07,307
Come on.

617
00:45:26,698 --> 00:45:28,336
Click.

618
00:45:32,898 --> 00:45:34,854
Are you hungry?

619
00:45:34,938 --> 00:45:36,337
No.

620
00:45:36,418 --> 00:45:40,457
If you like soda,
some doughnuts or something.

621
00:45:40,538 --> 00:45:43,052
I got a couple of cupcakes, huh?

622
00:45:43,178 --> 00:45:47,012
I think I got some
chocolate in there. No?

623
00:45:54,618 --> 00:45:56,893
Hot in here, you know?

624
00:45:59,058 --> 00:46:01,253
I could go for some music.

625
00:46:08,138 --> 00:46:10,527
These are the exotic animals.

626
00:46:10,618 --> 00:46:13,132
These are my friends
Cuff and Link.

627
00:46:13,218 --> 00:46:16,767
- I sold them to you.
- I know you did.

628
00:46:16,858 --> 00:46:21,648
The first day you worked
at that pet shop,

629
00:46:21,738 --> 00:46:23,808
I bought both these animals.

630
00:46:23,898 --> 00:46:27,334
I bought this bowl
and I bought the animals,

631
00:46:27,418 --> 00:46:30,057
some food, the marbles.

632
00:46:30,138 --> 00:46:31,776
Remember that mountain?

633
00:46:31,858 --> 00:46:35,373
I got rid of it
'cause it kept falling over.

634
00:46:38,178 --> 00:46:41,614
Why don't you come
over here and sit down?

635
00:46:42,298 --> 00:46:44,175
It's a nice couch.

636
00:46:44,298 --> 00:46:45,651
I don't know.

637
00:46:47,858 --> 00:46:50,691
There's big bugs there.
It's safer here.

638
00:46:52,858 --> 00:46:54,894
You want to sit down?

639
00:47:00,658 --> 00:47:02,933
These your parents?

640
00:47:03,018 --> 00:47:04,770
Yeah, that's them.

641
00:47:04,858 --> 00:47:07,736
- Is this you?
- Yeah. I was eight.

642
00:47:07,818 --> 00:47:10,286
The ltalian Stallion as a baby.

643
00:47:12,218 --> 00:47:16,450
Why don't you come on over
and make yourself comfortable?

644
00:47:20,578 --> 00:47:22,409
Do you have a phone?

645
00:47:22,498 --> 00:47:27,208
No. I had it pulled 'cause
people calling all the time.

646
00:47:27,298 --> 00:47:29,573
Who needs the aggravation?

647
00:47:29,658 --> 00:47:31,774
Who did you want to call?

648
00:47:31,858 --> 00:47:34,213
I want to call my brother.

649
00:47:35,338 --> 00:47:36,566
Why?

650
00:47:37,818 --> 00:47:39,809
I think he might be worried.

651
00:47:39,898 --> 00:47:42,537
I'll call your brother.

652
00:47:45,058 --> 00:47:50,371
Paulie, your sister's with me!
I'll call youse later.

653
00:47:56,058 --> 00:47:58,652
You don't like the room, do you?

654
00:47:58,738 --> 00:48:02,094
- It's fine.
- It's only temporary.

655
00:48:02,178 --> 00:48:04,169
It's not that.

656
00:48:07,978 --> 00:48:10,014
What's the problem?

657
00:48:10,098 --> 00:48:13,647
You don't like me?
You don't like the turtles?

658
00:48:13,738 --> 00:48:17,128
- I don't think I belong here.
- It's OK.

659
00:48:18,778 --> 00:48:20,734
I don't belong here.

660
00:48:21,578 --> 00:48:24,650
Well, it's OK,
'cause you're my guest.

661
00:48:25,818 --> 00:48:28,616
I don't know you well enough.

662
00:48:28,698 --> 00:48:32,373
I've never been
in a man's apartment alone.

663
00:48:33,218 --> 00:48:37,097
Well, they're all
the same, you know?

664
00:48:40,658 --> 00:48:43,934
I'm not sure
I know you well enough.

665
00:48:44,938 --> 00:48:47,532
I don't feel comfortable.

666
00:48:47,618 --> 00:48:50,735
Yo, Adrian, I ain't
so comfortable, either.

667
00:48:51,858 --> 00:48:54,975
- I should go.
- Don't go, please.

668
00:49:02,298 --> 00:49:04,095
Do me a favour.

669
00:49:04,178 --> 00:49:06,976
- What?
- Take off these glasses.

670
00:49:10,098 --> 00:49:12,896
You have nice eyes, you know?

671
00:49:14,338 --> 00:49:16,454
Do me another favour.

672
00:49:16,538 --> 00:49:19,610
Why don't you
take off that hat?

673
00:49:25,298 --> 00:49:28,210
I always knew you was pretty.

674
00:49:28,578 --> 00:49:31,968
- Don't tease me.
- I'm not teasing you.

675
00:49:37,738 --> 00:49:40,411
I just...want to kiss you.

676
00:49:42,378 --> 00:49:47,327
You don't have to kiss me back,
but I want to kiss you.

677
00:50:57,098 --> 00:51:01,137
- You got a fight coming up?
- Yeah, next month.

678
00:51:01,218 --> 00:51:05,928
Come to the gym, man.
We'll get you in shape.

679
00:51:06,018 --> 00:51:10,409
Rock, how are you doing?
Mick was looking for you.

680
00:51:10,498 --> 00:51:14,696
- For me? You sure?
- Yeah, he was looking for you.

681
00:51:14,778 --> 00:51:19,294
Your name's Rocky, right?
All right. Go on.

682
00:51:33,578 --> 00:51:35,455
You got something for me?

683
00:51:35,538 --> 00:51:39,451
Yeah, they need sparring
partners for Apollo Creed.

684
00:51:39,538 --> 00:51:41,893
- Here's the card.
- When was they here?

685
00:51:41,978 --> 00:51:43,457
About an hour ago.

686
00:51:43,538 --> 00:51:46,211
They probably need
sparring partners.

687
00:51:46,298 --> 00:51:48,573
I said that, you dumb dago!

688
00:51:50,018 --> 00:51:54,614
For six years you've been
sticking it to me. How come?

689
00:51:54,698 --> 00:51:57,610
- You don't want to know.
- I want to know.

690
00:51:57,698 --> 00:52:00,576
- You want to know?
- I want to know!

691
00:52:00,658 --> 00:52:02,330
OK, I'll tell you.

692
00:52:02,418 --> 00:52:05,694
You had the talent
to be a good fighter,

693
00:52:05,778 --> 00:52:09,657
not a leg-breaker
for some cheap loan-shark.

694
00:52:09,738 --> 00:52:11,649
It's a living.

695
00:52:11,738 --> 00:52:13,456
It's a waste of life.

696
00:52:30,910 --> 00:52:33,424
Yes, may I help you?

697
00:52:38,190 --> 00:52:40,545
You must be Mr Rocky Balboa.

698
00:52:40,630 --> 00:52:43,781
Mr Jergens is expecting you.
Just a moment.

699
00:52:47,950 --> 00:52:50,669
Mr Rocky Balboa to see you, sir.

700
00:52:52,630 --> 00:52:54,541
Please go in, Mr Balboa.

701
00:52:54,630 --> 00:52:56,825
- Can I have that?
- Certainly.

702
00:52:56,910 --> 00:52:58,309
Thanks.

703
00:53:03,750 --> 00:53:07,504
How are you? George Jergens.
Take a chair, please.

704
00:53:07,590 --> 00:53:09,023
Thanks.

705
00:53:10,350 --> 00:53:14,025
- Mr Balboa.
- Call me Rocky.

706
00:53:14,110 --> 00:53:17,386
Tell me, Rocky,
do you have a manager?

707
00:53:17,470 --> 00:53:19,586
Uh, no. Just me.

708
00:53:20,630 --> 00:53:24,782
Well, Rocky, I've got
a proposition to make to you.

709
00:53:24,870 --> 00:53:28,101
- About sparring?
- I beg your pardon.

710
00:53:28,190 --> 00:53:31,148
I know you're looking
for sparring partners.

711
00:53:31,230 --> 00:53:34,461
- I'm very available.
- I'm sure you are.

712
00:53:34,550 --> 00:53:38,179
Sparring with the champion
would be an honour,

713
00:53:38,270 --> 00:53:40,579
and I wouldn't take
no cheap shots.

714
00:53:40,670 --> 00:53:45,346
You don't understand me, Rocky.
My proposition's this...

715
00:53:45,430 --> 00:53:48,706
Would you be interested
in fighting Apollo Creed

716
00:53:48,790 --> 00:53:51,987
for the world
heavyweight championship?

717
00:53:55,190 --> 00:53:56,748
No.

718
00:53:57,110 --> 00:54:01,069
Listen, Rocky,
Apollo's seen you fight.

719
00:54:01,950 --> 00:54:05,306
He likes you.
He wants to fight you.

720
00:54:05,390 --> 00:54:08,348
It's just that,
I fight in clubs.

721
00:54:08,430 --> 00:54:10,341
I'm really a ham and egger.

722
00:54:10,430 --> 00:54:14,867
This guy's the best.
It wouldn't be a good fight.

723
00:54:14,950 --> 00:54:17,589
Thank you very much.
I appreciate it.

724
00:54:17,670 --> 00:54:22,061
Rocky, do you believe America
is the land of opportunity?.

725
00:54:22,950 --> 00:54:24,178
Yeah.

726
00:54:24,710 --> 00:54:28,305
Apollo Creed does,
and he's going to prove it

727
00:54:28,390 --> 00:54:31,666
by giving an unknown
a shot at the title,

728
00:54:31,750 --> 00:54:34,264
and that unknown is you.

729
00:54:34,350 --> 00:54:36,466
He picked you, Rocky.

730
00:54:36,550 --> 00:54:40,179
Rocky, it's the chance
of a lifetime.

731
00:54:41,030 --> 00:54:45,069
You can't pass it by.
What do you say?

732
00:54:50,741 --> 00:54:54,177
We want to ask Apollo
a few questions.

733
00:54:54,261 --> 00:54:57,776
How do you like the City
of Brotherly Love?

734
00:54:57,861 --> 00:55:01,297
Just being in Philadelphia
makes me feel patriotic.

735
00:55:01,381 --> 00:55:04,100
Beautiful people
and beautiful city.

736
00:55:04,181 --> 00:55:06,695
I'm proud to be an American.

737
00:55:06,781 --> 00:55:08,772
Apollo, why did you agree

738
00:55:08,861 --> 00:55:11,898
to fight a man who has
no chance of winning?

739
00:55:11,981 --> 00:55:13,892
American history proves

740
00:55:13,981 --> 00:55:17,940
that everybody's
got a chance to win.

741
00:55:18,021 --> 00:55:21,570
Didn't you ever hear
of Bunker Hill?

742
00:55:21,661 --> 00:55:27,258
Apollo, is it coincidence that
you're fighting a white man?

743
00:55:27,341 --> 00:55:32,574
Is it a coincidence
that he's fighting a black man?

744
00:55:34,741 --> 00:55:38,700
Apollo, how do you feel
about your challenger?

745
00:55:38,781 --> 00:55:41,341
Come here, Rock. My main man.

746
00:55:41,421 --> 00:55:44,458
- Rocky, ain't you ltalian?
- Yeah, I'm ltalian.

747
00:55:44,541 --> 00:55:48,500
If he can't fight,
I bet he can cook.

748
00:55:50,021 --> 00:55:52,535
His lungs, punch out.

749
00:55:54,061 --> 00:55:57,849
Rocky, how do you expect
to fight Apollo Creed?

750
00:55:57,941 --> 00:56:01,820
Creed's the best.
I'll do the best I can.

751
00:56:01,901 --> 00:56:03,857
Rocky, just between us,

752
00:56:03,941 --> 00:56:07,411
where did you get
the name ltalian Stallion?

753
00:56:07,501 --> 00:56:11,699
I invented that eight years ago
when I was eating dinner.

754
00:56:11,781 --> 00:56:15,660
Rocky, your pay-day
will be $1 50,000.

755
00:56:15,741 --> 00:56:17,572
Any comment?

756
00:56:18,941 --> 00:56:21,535
You got no comment,
Rocky, right?

757
00:56:21,621 --> 00:56:23,771
- No.
